# Rep Vault Architecture Defaults

- Use Next.js App Router patterns in `src/app`.
- Keep server-side data access on server components and server actions.
- Use Prisma as the only ORM and PostgreSQL as the runtime database provider.
- Keep feature behavior user-scoped unless a route is explicitly public.
- Prefer small reusable functions for domain logic that may be shared across pages/actions.
- Keep auth and onboarding invariants consistent with middleware gating.
